				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'd agree with the layout proposed by tepples but why ignore the 2048 first bytes ? Why not just the first $17 bytes, which are used by the CPU registers ?
<br />
<br />Ok, someone will answer "because with some shematic [....] it will ignore the first 2048 bytes". Ok, ok, but that doesn't mean all super-NROM carts would use this schematic. I'm pretty sure it's possible to decode the ROM at $4018-$ffff with a single PAL/GAL chip easily - and those aren't more expensive than 74xxx chips.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
